{
  "id": "ALSA-2025:A006",
  "summary": "Important: libblockdev security update",
  "details": "libblockdev is a C library supporting GObject introspection for manipulation of block devices. It has a plugin-based architecture where each technology (like LVM, Btrfs, MD RAID, Swap,...) is implemented in a separate plugin, possibly with multiple implementations (e.g. using LVM CLI or the new LVM DBus API).\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libblockdev: Due to the way libblockdev interacts with the udisks daemon, an \"allow_active\" user on a system may be able escalate to full root privileges on the target host. (CVE-2025-6019)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
  "modified": "2025-06-20T15:10:26Z",
